will show nothing because no container is running.

To run the container again

You run the same command:

docker run --rm \
    -v "$(pwd):/downloads" \
    jauderho/yt-dlp \
    -f "bv*+ba/b" \
    --merge-output-format mp4 \
    "https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/introvideos/versioncontrol"

Docker will:

Find image jauderho/yt-dlp
Create a new container
Run yt-dlp inside the container
Download the video
Remove the container because of --rm

